t-focus\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":77,"totalLines":77,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","time":{"start":1782532193648,"end":1782532193656}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9d95d13d2e2101016a3f486191708191b914ecd225c72498"}},"id":"prt_f0732bd6e001L2rfep9dZRizMm","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f073271a7001sFCL0mIWZqOuse"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532193660,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sp10rq7n8jRRaU0kkTMC8Qqb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1782532193642,"end":1782532193658}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9d95d13d2e2101016a3f486191648191af35828ec4bdca9a"}},"id":"prt_f0732bd690010NFQtWF2tmC9Ye","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f073271a7001sFCL0mIWZqOuse"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532193660,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cQ6wfaBvcU3j0IxPrmwMQp8z","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 2. TOPIC\n36: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n41: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n42: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n43: - [ ] [Question 2]\n44: - [ ] [Question 3]\n45: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n50: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n55: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n60: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n61: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n67: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n68: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n69: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n70: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n71: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n76: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n77: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n78: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n84: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n85: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n86: \n87: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n88: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n89: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n90: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n91: \n92: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n93: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n94: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n95: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n100: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n101: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n102: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n103: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n108: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n109: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n110: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n115: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n116: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n117: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n122: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n123: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n128: - Max iterations: [from config]\n129: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n130: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n131: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n132: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n133: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n134: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n135: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n136: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n137: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n138: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n139: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n140: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 140 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":140,"totalLines":140,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1782532193651,"end":1782532193659}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9d95d13d2e2101016a3f486191788191bd535b91c281c309"}},"id":"prt_f0732bd71001Wh8zgO7eBk9dMI","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f073271a7001sFCL0mIWZqOuse"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532193668,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_pWk6Wh0hvcKHj1f6a01yAm3T","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","offset":1,"limit":280},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Signals Reference\n3: description: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence signals\"\n6:   - \"research new info ratio\"\n7:   - \"research stuck count\"\n8:   - \"mad noise floor\"\n9:   - \"question entropy\"\n10:   - \"research composite score\"\n11:   - \"convergence threshold tuning\"\n12: importance_tier: normal\n13: contextType: implementation\n14: version: 1.14.0.3\n15: ---\n16: \n17: # Convergence Signals Reference\n18: \n19: This reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n24: \n25: ### Purpose\n26: \n27: Define the live convergence signals, scoring rules, threshold semantics, and reporting shape used by deep-research loops.\n28: \n29: ### When to Use\n30: \n31: Load this reference when calculating `newInfoRatio`, explaining a composite STOP vote, debugging stuck counts, or validating convergence dashboards.\n32: \n33: ### Core Principle\n34: \n35: Signals nominate STOP; legal-stop and graph gates authorize or block it.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 2. SIGNAL MODEL\n40: \n41: The live model uses three weighted signals and normalizes by the weight of the signals that have enough data to run.\n42: \n43: | Signal | Weight | Requires | STOP Vote |\n44: |--------|--------|----------|-----------|\n45: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Average of last 3 `newInfoRatio` values is below `convergenceThreshold` |\n46: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Latest `newInfoRatio` is at or below `MAD * 1.4826` |\n47: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | At least 1 key question | Evidence-backed coverage is at least `0.85` |\n48: \n49: `thought` iterations are excluded from rolling average, MAD, and stuck counting because they are analytical-only. `insight` iterations are included in convergence signals but do not count as stuck.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 3. NEW INFO RATIO\n54: \n55: `newInfoRatio` measures how much an iteration added relative to accumulated research knowledge.\n56: \n57: | Ratio | Meaning |\n58: |-------|---------|\n59: | `1.0` | Mostly new findings or first broad pass |\n60: | `0.7` | Several new findings plus some refinements |\n61: | `0.5` | Mixed new and repeated material |\n62: | `0.2` | Mostly confirmation or marginal novelty |\n63: | `0.0` | No new information |\n64: \n65: Agent assessment guidance:\n66: \n67: - Fully new finding: count as `1.0`.\n68: - Refinement of known finding: count as partial novelty.\n69: - Ruled-out direction: count as valuable negative knowledge when it removes a plausible path.\n70: - Tentative single-source finding: contribute less than verified or multi-source evidence.\n71: - Simplicity bonus may add up to `0.10`, capped at `1.0`, when an iteration materially reduces the search space.\n72: \n73: Every iteration record should include `newInfoRatio` and `noveltyJustification`; see `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 4. STUCK COUNT\n78: \n79: `stuckCount` is consecutive no-progress evidence iterations.\n80: \n81: ```text\n82: for each iteration from newest to oldest:\n83:   skip status == \"thought\"\n84:   stop counting when status == \"insight\"\n85:   count if status == \"stuck\" or newInfoRatio <= noProgressThreshold\n86:   stop counting on any productive evidence iteration\n87: ```\n88: \n89: Default threshold behavior:\n90: \n91: - `stuckThreshold`: `3`\n92: - `noProgressThreshold`: implementation default aligned with the workflow's recovery check\n93: - Recovery route: `convergence_recovery.md`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## 5. ROLLING AVERAGE\n98: \n99: Rolling average uses the last three evidence iterations.\n100: \n101: ```text\n102: evidenceIterations = iterations where status != \"thought\"\n103: recent = last 3 evidenceIterations\n104: rollingAvg = mean(recent.newInfoRatio)\n105: rollingStop = rollingAvg < convergenceThreshold\n106: ```\n107: \n108: This signal is unavailable before three evidence iterations. The composite vote normalizes over active signals, so early runs can still use question coverage without pretending the rolling signal exists.\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 6. MAD NOISE FLOOR\n113: \n114: MAD compares the latest ratio against the noise floor in the accumulated evidence ratios.\n115: \n116: ```text\n117: ratios = evidenceIterations.newInfoRatio\n118: medianRatio = median(ratios)\n119: mad = median(abs(ratio - medianRatio) for ratio in ratios)\n120: noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826\n121: madStop = latestEvidenceRatio <= noiseFloor\n122: ```\n123: \n124: Interpretation:\n125: \n126: | Condition | Meaning |\n127: |-----------|---------|\n128: | Latest ratio above floor | Signal still exceeds observed noise |\n129: | Latest ratio within floor | New findings may be indistinguishable from noise |\n130: | Very high floor | Iteration quality is unstable; narrow the focus before trusting STOP |\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## 7. QUESTION ENTROPY\n135: \n136: Question entropy is evidence-backed key-question coverage.\n137: \n138: ```text\n139: answered = count(keyQuestions with evidence-backed answers)\n140: total = count(keyQuestions)\n141: coverage = answered / total\n142: entropyStop = coverage >= 0.85\n143: ```\n144: \n145: Tentative-only findings do not satisfy evidence-backed coverage. Graph events may add extra STOP blockers when graph coverage disagrees with inline question coverage; see `convergence_graph.md`.\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 8. COMPOSITE SCORE\n150: \n151: ```text\n152: activeSignals = signals with enough data\n153: stopScore = sum(signal.weight for active STOP votes) / sum(active signal weights)\n154: stopCandidate = stopScore > 0.60\n155: ```\n156: \n157: The score nominates STOP only. `convergence.md` defines the legal-stop gates that decide whether the loop may exit.\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## 9. REPORTING\n162: \n163: Every completed loop should report:\n164: \n165: ```text\n166: CONVERGENCE REPORT\n167: ------------------\n168: Stop reason: converged | maxIterationsReached | userPaused | stuckRecovery | error\n169: Iterations completed: N\n170: Questions answered: X/Y\n171: Average newInfoRatio trend: [...]\n172: Composite stop score: 0.XX\n173: Signals:\n174:   Rolling Avg (w=0.30): STOP|CONTINUE\n175:   MAD Noise (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\n176:   Entropy (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\n177: Legal-stop gates: pass|blocked\n178: Graph gates: pass|blocked|not_applicable\n179: ```\n180: \n181: Dashboard and registry fields derived from these signals are documented in `../state/state_reducer_registry.md`.\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 10. THRESHOLD TUNING\n186: \n187: | Goal | Adjustment |\n188: |------|------------|\n189: | Deeper research | Lower `convergenceThreshold`, raise `maxIterations` |\n190: | Faster completion | Raise `convergenceThreshold`, lower `maxIterations` |\n191: | More stuck recovery | Lower `stuckThreshold` cautiously |\n192: | Fewer false stops | Keep legal-stop and graph gates enabled |\n193: \n194: Optimizer-managed fields are described in `convergence_reference_only.md`. Optimizer proposals are advisory and do not override locked stop-contract fields.\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Signals Reference\ndescription: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence signals\"\n  - \"research new info ratio\"\n  - \"research stuck count\"\n  - \"mad noise floor\"\n  - \"question entropy\"\n  - \"research composite score\"\n  - \"convergence threshold tuning\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Convergence Signals Reference\n\nThis reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Signals Reference\ndescription: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence signals\"\n  - \"research new info ratio\"\n  - \"research stuck count\"\n  - \"mad noise floor\"\n  - \"question entropy\"\n  - \"research composite score\"\n  - \"convergence threshold tuning\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Convergence Signals Reference\n\nThis reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the live convergence signals, scoring rules, threshold semantics, and reporting shape used by deep-research loops.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when calculating `newInfoRatio`, explaining a composite STOP vote, debugging stuck counts, or validating convergence dashboards.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nSignals nominate STOP; legal-stop and graph gates authorize or block it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SIGNAL MODEL\n\nThe live model uses three weighted signals and normalizes by the weight of the signals that have enough data to run.\n\n| Signal | Weight | Requires | STOP Vote |\n|--------|--------|----------|-----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Average of last 3 `newInfoRatio` values is below `convergenceThreshold` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Latest `newInfoRatio` is at or below `MAD * 1.4826` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | At least 1 key question | Evidence-backed coverage is at least `0.85` |\n\n`thought` iterations are excluded from rolling average, MAD, and stuck counting because they are analytical-only. `insight` iterations are included in convergence signals but do not count as stuck.\n\n---\n\n## 3. NEW INFO RATIO\n\n`newInfoRatio` measures how much an iteration added relative to accumulated research knowledge.\n\n| Ratio | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `1.0` | Mostly new findings or first broad pass |\n| `0.7` | Several new findings plus some refinements |\n| `0.5` | Mixed new and repeated material |\n| `0.2` | Mostly confirmation or marginal novelty |\n| `0.0` | No new information |\n\nAgent assessment guidance:\n\n- Fully new finding: count as `1.0`.\n- Refinement of known finding: count as partial novelty.\n- Ruled-out direction: count as valuable negative knowledge when it removes a plausible path.\n- Tentative single-source finding: contribute less than verified or multi-source evidence.\n- Simplicity bonus may add up to `0.10`, capped at `1.0`, when an iteration materially reduces the search space.\n\nEvery iteration record should include `newInfoRatio` and `noveltyJustification`; see `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STUCK COUNT\n\n`stuckCount` is consecutive no-progress evidence iterations.\n\n```text\nfor each iteration from newest to oldest:\n  skip status == \"thought\"\n  stop counting when status == \"insight\"\n  count if status == \"stuck\" or newInfoRatio <= noProgressThreshold\n  stop counting on any productive evidence iteration\n```\n\nDefault threshold behavior:\n\n- `stuckThreshold`: `3`\n- `noProgressThreshold`: implementation default aligned with the workflow's recovery check\n- Recovery route: `convergence_recovery.md`\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROLLING AVERAGE\n\nRolling average uses the last three evidence iterations.\n\n```text\nevidenceIterations = iterations where status != \"thought\"\nrecent = last 3 evidenceIterations\nrollingAvg = mean(recent.newInfoRatio)\nrollingStop = rollingAvg < convergenceThreshold\n```\n\nThis signal is unavailable before three evidence iterations. The composite vote normalizes over active signals, so early runs can still use question coverage without pretending the rolling signal exists.\n\n---\n\n## 6. MAD NOISE FLOOR\n\nMAD compares the latest ratio against the noise floor in the accumulated evidence ratios.\n\n```text\nratios = evidenceIterations.newInfoRatio\nmedianRatio = median(ratios)\nmad = median(abs(ratio - medianRatio) for ratio in ratios)\nnoiseFloor = mad * 1.4826\nmadStop = latestEvidenceRatio <= noiseFloor\n```\n\nInterpretation:\n\n| Condition | Meaning |\n|-----------|---------|\n| Latest ratio above floor | Signal still exceeds observed noise |\n| Latest ratio within floor | New findings may be indistinguishable from noise |\n| Very high floor | Iteration quality is unstable; narrow the focus before trusting STOP |\n\n---\n\n## 7. QUESTION ENTROPY\n\nQuestion entropy is evidence-backed key-question coverage.\n\n```text\nanswered = count(keyQuestions with evidence-backed answers)\ntotal = count(keyQuestions)\ncoverage = answered / total\nentropyStop = coverage >= 0.85\n```\n\nTentative-only findings do not satisfy evidence-backed coverage. Graph events may add extra STOP blockers when graph coverage disagrees with inline question coverage; see `convergence_graph.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. COMPOSITE SCORE\n\n```text\nactiveSignals = signals with enough data\nstopScore = sum(signal.weight for active STOP votes) / sum(active signal weights)\nstopCandidate = stopScore > 0.60\n```\n\nThe score nominates STOP only. `convergence.md` defines the legal-stop gates that decide whether the loop may exit.\n\n---\n\n## 9. REPORTING\n\nEvery completed loop should report:\n\n```text\nCONVERGENCE REPORT\n------------------\nStop reason: converged | maxIterationsReached | userPaused | stuckRecovery | error\nIterations completed: N\nQuestions answered: X/Y\nAverage newInfoRatio trend: [...]\nComposite stop score: 0.XX\nSignals:\n  Rolling Avg (w=0.30): STOP|CONTINUE\n  MAD Noise (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\n  Entropy (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\nLegal-stop gates: pass|blocked\nGraph gates: pass|blocked|not_applicable\n```\n\nDashboard and registry fields derived from these signals are documented in `../state/state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 10. THRESHOLD TUNING\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper research | Lower `convergenceThreshold`, raise `maxIterations` |\n| Faster completion | Raise `convergenceThreshold`, lower `maxIterations` |\n| More stuck recovery | Lower `stuckThreshold` cautiously |\n| Fewer false stops | Keep legal-stop and graph gates enabled |\n\nOptimizer-managed fields are described in `convergence_reference_only.md`. Optimizer proposals are advisory and do not override locked stop-contract fields.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":194,"totalLines":194,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","time":{"start":1782532193645,"end":1782532193666}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9d95d13d2e2101016a3f4861916c8191b1eab930bd3f48de"}},"id":"prt_f0732bd6c001eGzkrXpLnrTFSW","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f073271a7001sFCL0mIWZqOuse"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532193670,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jtA730HF1tuSW3z2gHqFMU6m","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n102:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n103:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n104:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n105:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n106:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n107:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n108:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n109:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n110:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n111:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n112:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n113:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n114:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n115:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n116:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n117:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n118:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n119:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n120: \n121: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n122: # WORKFLOW\n123: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n124: workflow:\n125: \n126:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n127:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n128:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n129:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n130:     if_present:\n131:       bind:\n132:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n133:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n134:         artifact_subfolder: null\n135:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n136:     if_absent:\n137:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n138:       outputs:\n139:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n140:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n141:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n142:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n143: \n144:   step_fanout_spawn:\n145:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n146:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n147:     instructions: |\n148:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n149:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n150:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n151:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n152:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n153:     sub_steps:\n154:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n155:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n156:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n157:         command: |\n158:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n159:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n160:             --loop-type research \\\n161:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n162:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n163:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n164:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n165:         wait_for_completion: true\n166:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n167:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n168:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n169:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n170:         dispatch:\n171:           agent: deep-research\n172:           model: opus\n173:           context: |\n174:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n175:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n176:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n177:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n178:               executor: native\n179:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n180:         wait_for_completion: true\n181: \n182:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n183:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n184:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n185:   phase_init:\n186:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n187:     steps:\n188: \n189:       step_preflight_contract:\n190:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n191:         verify:\n192:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n193:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n194:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n195:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n196:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n197: \n198:       step_create_directories:\n199:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n200:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n201: \n202:       step_detect_resource_map:\n203:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n204:         inspect:\n205:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n206:         classify:\n207:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n208:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n209:         outputs:\n210:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n211:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n212: \n213:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n214:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n215:         inspect_legacy:\n216:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n217:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n220:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n221:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n222:         on_legacy_read:\n223:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n224: \n225:       step_acquire_lock:\n226:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n227:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n228:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n229:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n230:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n231:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n232:         on_halt:\n233:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n234:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n235:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n236:         on_cancel:\n237:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n238:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n239:         on_workflow_exit:\n240:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n241:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n242: \n243:       step_classify_session:\n244:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n245:         inspect:\n246:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n247:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n248:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n249:         classify:\n250:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n251:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n252:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n253:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n254:         outputs:\n255:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n256:         on_resume:\n257:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n258:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n259:           gate3_classification: write-path\n260:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n261:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n262:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n263:           skip_to: phase_loop\n264:         on_restart:\n265:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n266:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n267:           set:\n268:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n269:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n270:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n271:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n272:           skip_to: step_create_config\n273:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n274:         on_completed_session:\n275:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n276:           halt: true\n277:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n278:         on_invalid_state:\n279:           halt: true\n280:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n281:         on_fresh:\n282:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n283: \n284:       step_create_config:\n285:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n286:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n287:         populate:\n288:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n289:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n290:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n291:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n292:           stuckThreshold: 3\n293:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n294:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n295:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n296:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n297:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n298:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n299:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n300:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n301:           status: \"initialized\"\n302:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n303:           lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n304:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n305:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n306:           lineage.generation: 1\n307:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n308:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n309: \n310:       step_create_state_log:\n311:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n312:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n313:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n314:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n315:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n316: \n317:       step_create_strategy:\n318:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n319:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n320:         populate:\n321:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n322:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n323:           known_context: \"None\"\n324:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n325:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n326:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n327:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n328: \n329:       step_create_registry:\n330:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n331:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n332:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n333: \n334:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n335:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n336:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n337:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n338:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n339: \n340:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n341:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n342:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n343:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n344: \n345:       step_detect_spec_present:\n346:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n347:         inspect:\n348:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n349:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n350:         classify:\n351:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n352:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n353:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n354:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n355:         outputs:\n356:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n357:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n358:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n359: \n360:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n\n(Showing lines 1-360 of 1082. Use offset=361 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":360,"totalLines":1082,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782532193640,"end":1782532193669}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9d95d13d2e2101016a3f486191548191b3b0a274a6186cad"}},"id":"prt_f0732bd40001q3Uv1K8FHt33LD","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f073271a7001sFCL0mIWZqOuse"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532193682,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_KeOIemq4hKSgnlZajWzynn5q","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"deep-research: Manual Testing Playbook\"\n3: description: \"Operator-facing reference combining the manual testing directory, integrated review/orchestration guidance, execution expectations, and per-feature validation files for the deep-research skill.\"\n4: version: 1.14.0.20\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # deep-research: Manual Testing Playbook\n8: \n9: > **EXECUTION POLICY**: Every scenario MUST be executed for real — not mocked, not stubbed, not classified as \"unautomatable\". AI agents executing these scenarios must run the actual commands, inspect real files, call real handlers, and verify real outputs. The only acceptable classifications are PASS, FAIL, or SKIP (with a specific sandbox blocker documented). \"UNAUTOMATABLE\" is not a valid status.\n10: \n11: This document combines the manual testing contract for the `deep-research` skill into a single reference. The root playbook acts as the directory, review protocol, and orchestration guide while the per-feature files carry the scenario-specific execution truth.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: Canonical package artifacts:\n16: - `manual_testing_playbook.md`\n17: - `01--entry-points-and-modes/`\n18: - `02--initialization-and-state-setup/`\n19: - `03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/`\n20: - `04--convergence-and-recovery/`\n21: - `05--pause-resume-and-fault-tolerance/`\n22: - `06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/`\n23: - `07--command-flow-stress-tests/`\n24: - `08--fanout/`\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n29: \n30: This playbook provides 44 deterministic scenarios across 8 categories validating the current `deep-research` skill surface (35 DR-* feature scenarios + 6 CP-* command-flow stress tests + 3 fan-out scenarios). Each scenario maps to a dedicated feature file with the canonical objective, prompt summary, expected signals, and live source anchors.\n31: \n32: ### REALISTIC TEST MODEL\n33: \n34: 1. Start from the operator-visible research workflow, not a synthetic command matrix.\n35: 2. Validate public docs and command surfaces before deeper YAML or reducer contracts when that order matters.\n36: 3. Capture enough evidence that another operator can reproduce the verdict without re-deriving the scenario.\n37: 4. Report a concise user-facing verdict rather than raw implementation notes.\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 2. GLOBAL PRECONDITIONS\n42: \n43: - `deep-research` skill exists at `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/`.\n44: - `/deep:research` command exists at `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`.\n45: - `@deep-research` agent definition exists at `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md` plus runtime variants.\n46: - Deep-research YAML workflows and reducer/runtime assets are available in the repository.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 3. GLOBAL EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n51: \n52: - A PASS, PARTIAL, or FAIL verdict with reasoning.\n53: - Evidence captured from live file contents or generated artifacts.\n54: - Cross-source consistency checks across README, quick reference, command, YAML, and reducer/state assets.\n55: - The exact prompt used when orchestration behavior is part of the scenario.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 4. DETERMINISTIC COMMAND NOTATION\n60: \n61: - Use `rg`, `sed`, and direct artifact inspection to gather deterministic evidence.\n62: - Follow the prescribed order so user-facing documentation is checked before lower-level workflow contracts when sequencing matters.\n63: - Keep the final verdict tied to captured evidence instead of inferred runtime behavior.\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 5. REVIEW PROTOCOL AND RELEASE READINESS\n68: \n69: - A scenario is PASS only when the expected artifacts, prompts, workflow routing, and evidence all align.\n70: - The feature files remain the source of execution truth when the root summary is intentionally terse.\n71: - Release readiness depends on complete scenario coverage and no unresolved blocking contradictions.\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 6. SUB-AGENT ORCHESTRATION AND WAVE PLANNING\n76: \n77: - Wave 1 covers entrypoint and initialization checks.\n78: - Wave 2 covers iteration-state discipline and reducer/dashboard updates.\n79: - Wave 3 covers convergence, quality guards, and stuck recovery.\n80: - Wave 4 covers pause/resume, reconstruction, synthesis, memory save, and later-loop hardening.\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## 7. ENTRY POINTS AND MODES\n85: \n86: This category covers 3 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract.\n87: \n88: ### DR-001 | Auto mode deep-research kickoff\n89: \n90: #### Description\n91: Verify that autonomous mode is exposed consistently across the README, quick reference, command entrypoint, and auto YAML workflow.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario Contract\n94: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the autonomous entrypoint for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify /deep:research:auto is documented consistently across the README, quick reference, command entrypoint, and autonomous YAML workflow. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict with the expected artifact summary.\n95: \n96: Expected signals: The same autonomous command appears across sources, autonomous mode is approval-free, and the workflow points to config, JSONL, strategy, iteration files, and `research/research.md`.\n97: \n98: #### Test Execution\n99: > **Feature File:** [DR-001](01--entry-points-and-modes/auto-mode-deep-research-kickoff.md)\n100: \n101: ### DR-002 | Confirm mode checkpointed execution\n102: \n103: #### Description\n104: Verify that confirm mode adds approval checkpoints without changing the core loop phases or artifact contract.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario Contract\n107: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the confirm-mode contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify /deep:research:confirm is documented as interactive, approval-gated, and still uses the same core loop and output artifacts as auto mode. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n108: \n109: Expected signals: Confirm mode is interactive, approval-gated, and still routes through initialization, loop, synthesis, and save rather than a separate workflow.\n110: \n111: #### Test Execution\n112: > **Feature File:** [DR-002](01--entry-points-and-modes/confirm-mode-checkpointed-execution.md)\n113: \n114: ### DR-003 | Parameterized invocation with --max-iterations and --convergence\n115: \n116: #### Description\n117: Verify that the command binds topic, spec folder, execution mode, max iterations, and convergence threshold before the YAML workflow starts.\n118: \n119: #### Scenario Contract\n120: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the setup-binding contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify the command entrypoint gathers required values before loading YAML and that the YAML preflight rejects missing bindings or invalid spec-folder scope. Return a concise pass/fail verdict.\n121: \n122: Expected signals: The command explicitly names topic, spec folder, execution mode, max iterations, and convergence threshold; YAML preflight verifies them before file writes.\n123: \n124: #### Test Execution\n125: > **Feature File:** [DR-003](01--entry-points-and-modes/parameterized-invocation-max-iterations-convergence.md)\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## 8. INITIALIZATION AND STATE SETUP\n130: \n131: This category covers 4 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract.\n132: \n133: ### DR-004 | Fresh initialization creates canonical state files\n134: \n135: #### Description\n136: Verify that a fresh session creates the canonical config, JSONL, and strategy files from the shipped assets.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario Contract\n139: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the fresh-initialization contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify initialization creates deep-research-config.json, deep-research-state.jsonl, and deep-research-strategy.md from the live templates. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict.\n140: \n141: Expected signals: The scratch directory is created, config and strategy come from the shipped assets, and the JSONL begins with a config record.\n142: \n143: #### Test Execution\n144: > **Feature File:** [DR-004](02--initialization-and-state-setup/fresh-initialization-creates-canonical-state-files.md)\n145: \n146: ### DR-005 | Resume classification from valid prior state\n147: \n148: #### Description\n149: Verify that the workflow classifies an existing valid scratch state as resumable before writing new files.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario Contract\n152: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the resume-classification contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy are inspected before new files are written and that a valid prior state skips re-initialization. Return a concise pass/fail verdict.\n153: \n154: Expected signals: A four-state classification model exists, resume skips init writes, and completed sessions route differently from active resumes.\n155: \n156: #### Test Execution\n157: > **Feature File:** [DR-005](02--initialization-and-state-setup/resume-classification-from-valid-prior-state.md)\n158: \n159: ### DR-006 | Invalid or contradictory state halts for repair\n160: \n161: #### Description\n162: Verify that partial or contradictory scratch artifacts trigger a halt for repair instead of a guessed resume path.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario Contract\n165: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the invalid-state halt contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify contradictory or partial deep-research artifacts stop the workflow for repair instead of guessing through initialization. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict.\n166: \n167: Expected signals: Invalid-state is a named class, both YAML files halt with a repair message, and the docs do not promise silent guessing for contradictory state.\n168: \n169: #### Test Execution\n170: > **Feature File:** [DR-006](02--initialization-and-state-setup/invalid-or-contradictory-state-halts-for-repair.md)\n171: \n172: ### DR-027 | Research charter validated at init\n173: \n174: #### Description\n175: Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections after initialization.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario Contract\n178: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the research charter validation contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify initialization Step 5a verifies the presence of \"Non-Goals\" and \"Stop Conditions\" sections in strategy.md, appends empty placeholders if missing, and presents the charter for user review in confirm mode. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n179: \n180: Expected signals: strategy.md has a \"## 4. Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist); strategy.md has a \"## 5. Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist); if either section is missing, it is appended as an empty placeholder; in confirm mode, the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) is presented for user review before proceeding.\n181: \n182: #### Test Execution\n183: > **Feature File:** [DR-027](02--initialization-and-state-setup/research-charter-validation.md)\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## 9. ITERATION EXECUTION AND STATE DISCIPLINE\n188: \n189: This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract.\n190: \n191: ### DR-007 | Iteration reads state before research\n192: \n193: #### Description\n194: Verify that each dispatched iteration reads JSONL and strategy state before performing research actions.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario Contract\n197: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the read-state-first iteration contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify the loop dispatch and the @deep-research agent both require reading JSONL and strategy state before any research actions. Return a concise operator verdict.\n198: \n199: Expected signals: Loop step order begins with state reads, the quick reference checklist says the same, and the agent definition starts with JSONL plus strategy reads.\n200: \n201: #### Test Execution\n202: > **Feature File:** [DR-007](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/iteration-reads-state-before-research.md)\n203: \n204: ### DR-008 | Iteration writes iteration-NNN.md, JSONL record, and reducer refresh\n205: \n206: #### Description\n207: Verify that each completed iteration writes the detailed iteration file, appends JSONL, and enables reducer-owned packet synchronization.\n208: \n209: #### Scenario Contract\n210: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the iteration write-back contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify each iteration writes iteration-NNN.md, appends a JSONL iteration record, and triggers reducer-owned refresh of deep-research-strategy.md, findings-registry.json, and deep-research-dashboard.md. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n211: \n212: Expected signals: Iteration file creation, JSONL append, and reducer refresh are all mandatory parts of the loop, not optional side effects.\n213: \n214: #### Test Execution\n215: > **Feature File:** [DR-008](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/iteration-writes-iteration-jsonl-and-strategy-update.md)\n216: \n217: ### DR-009 | Strategy “Next Focus” and exhausted-approach discipline\n218: \n219: #### Description\n220: Verify that the loop honors the strategy file’s Next Focus and avoids approaches marked exhausted or blocked.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario Contract\n223: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the strategy-discipline contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify iteration focus comes from Next Focus and that exhausted or blocked approaches are not retried. Return a concise user-facing verdict.\n224: \n225: Expected signals: Next Focus is read explicitly, exhausted approaches are treated as do-not-retry, and recovery mode consults deferred ideas instead of repeating blocked tactics.\n226: \n227: #### Test Execution\n228: > **Feature File:** [DR-009](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/strategy-next-focus-and-exhausted-approach-discipline.md)\n229: \n230: ### DR-010 | Progressive synthesis behavior for research/research.md\n231: \n232: #### Description\n233: Verify that `research/research.md` remains workflow-owned while progressive updates are allowed when `progressiveSynthesis` is enabled.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario Contract\n236: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the progressive-synthesis contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify research/research.md is workflow-owned canonical output, that incremental updates are allowed when progressiveSynthesis is true, and that synthesis still finalizes the document. Return a concise verdict.\n237: \n238: Expected signals: The docs describe `research/research.md` as workflow-owned, `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to true, and the final synthesis phase still runs.\n239: \n240: #### Test Execution\n241: > **Feature File:** [DR-010](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/progressive-synthesis-behavior-for-research-md.md)\n242: \n243: ### DR-024 | Dashboard generation after iteration\n244: \n245: #### Description\n246: Verify dashboard.md is auto-generated after iteration evaluation with correct content.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario Contract\n249: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the dashboard generation contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify the dashboard file is created at the correct path, contains the required sections (iteration table, question status, trend, dead ends, next focus, active risks), and is regenerated after each iteration. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n250: \n251: Expected signals: `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` exists after at least one iteration completes, contains an iteration table, question status with X/Y answered, trend with last 3 newInfoRatio values, dead ends consolidated from ruledOut data, next focus from strategy.md, and active risks.\n252: \n253: #### Test Execution\n254: > **Feature File:** [DR-024](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/dashboard-generation-after-iteration.md)\n255: \n256: ### DR-025 | Novelty justification present in JSONL\n257: \n258: #### Description\n259: Verify every iteration JSONL record includes noveltyJustification alongside newInfoRatio.\n260: \n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 683. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"deep-research: Manual Testing Playbook\"\ndescription: \"Operator-facing reference combining the manual testing directory, integrated review/orchestration guidance, execution expectations, and per-feature validation files for the deep-research skill.\"\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# deep-research: Manual Testing Playbook\n\n> **EXECUTION POLICY**: Every scenario MUST be executed for real — not mocked, not stubbed, not classified as \"unautomatable\". AI agents executing these scenarios must run the actual commands, inspect real files, call real handlers, and verify real outputs. The only acceptable classifications are PASS, FAIL, or SKIP (with a specific sandbox blocker documented). \"UNAUTOMATABLE\" is not a valid status.\n\nThis document combines the manual testing contract for the `deep-research` skill into a single reference. The root playbook acts as the directory, review protocol, and orchestration guide while the per-feature files carry the scenario-specific execution truth.\n\n---\n\nCanonical package artifacts:\n- `manual_testing_playbook.md`\n- `01--entry-points-and-modes/`\n- `02--initialization-and-state-setup/`\n- `03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/`\n- `04--convergence-and-recovery/`","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"deep-research: Manual Testing Playbook\"\ndescription: \"Operator-facing reference combining the manual testing directory, integrated review/orchestration guidance, execution expectations, and per-feature validation files for the deep-research skill.\"\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# deep-research: Manual Testing Playbook\n\n> **EXECUTION POLICY**: Every scenario MUST be executed for real — not mocked, not stubbed, not classified as \"unautomatable\". AI agents executing these scenarios must run the actual commands, inspect real files, call real handlers, and verify real outputs. The only acceptable classifications are PASS, FAIL, or SKIP (with a specific sandbox blocker documented). \"UNAUTOMATABLE\" is not a valid status.\n\nThis document combines the manual testing contract for the `deep-research` skill into a single reference. The root playbook acts as the directory, review protocol, and orchestration guide while the per-feature files carry the scenario-specific execution truth.\n\n---\n\nCanonical package artifacts:\n- `manual_testing_playbook.md`\n- `01--entry-points-and-modes/`\n- `02--initialization-and-state-setup/`\n- `03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/`\n- `04--convergence-and-recovery/`\n- `05--pause-resume-and-fault-tolerance/`\n- `06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/`\n- `07--command-flow-stress-tests/`\n- `08--fanout/`\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis playbook provides 44 deterministic scenarios across 8 categories validating the current `deep-research` skill surface (35 DR-* feature scenarios + 6 CP-* command-flow stress tests + 3 fan-out scenarios). Each scenario maps to a dedicated feature file with the canonical objective, prompt summary, expected signals, and live source anchors.\n\n### REALISTIC TEST MODEL\n\n1. Start from the operator-visible research workflow, not a synthetic command matrix.\n2. Validate public docs and command surfaces before deeper YAML or reducer contracts when that order matters.\n3. Capture enough evidence that another operator can reproduce the verdict without re-deriving the scenario.\n4. Report a concise user-facing verdict rather than raw implementation notes.\n\n---\n\n## 2. GLOBAL PRECONDITIONS\n\n- `deep-research` skill exists at `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/`.\n- `/deep:research` command exists at `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`.\n- `@deep-research` agent definition exists at `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md` plus runtime variants.\n- Deep-research YAML workflows and reducer/runtime assets are available in the repository.\n\n---\n\n## 3. GLOBAL EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n\n- A PASS, PARTIAL, or FAIL verdict with reasoning.\n- Evidence captured from live file contents or generated artifacts.\n- Cross-source consistency checks across README, quick reference, command, YAML, and reducer/state assets.\n- The exact prompt used when orchestration behavior is part of the scenario.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DETERMINISTIC COMMAND NOTATION\n\n- Use `rg`, `sed`, and direct artifact inspection to gather deterministic evidence.\n- Follow the prescribed order so user-facing documentation is checked before lower-level workflow contracts when sequencing matters.\n- Keep the final verdict tied to captured evidence instead of inferred runtime behavior.\n\n---\n\n## 5. REVIEW PROTOCOL AND RELEASE READINESS\n\n- A scenario is PASS only when the expected artifacts, prompts, workflow routing, and evidence all align.\n- The feature files remain the source of execution truth when the root summary is intentionally terse.\n- Release readiness depends on complete scenario coverage and no unresolved blocking contradictions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUB-AGENT ORCHESTRATION AND WAVE PLANNING\n\n- Wave 1 covers entrypoint and initialization checks.\n- Wave 2 covers iteration-state discipline and reducer/dashboard updates.\n- Wave 3 covers convergence, quality guards, and stuck recovery.\n- Wave 4 covers pause/resume, reconstruction, synthesis, memory save, and later-loop hardening.\n\n---\n\n## 7. ENTRY POINTS AND MODES\n\nThis category covers 3 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract.\n\n### DR-001 | Auto mode deep-research kickoff\n\n#### Description\nVerify that autonomous mode is exposed consistently across the README, quick reference, command entrypoint, and auto YAML workflow.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the autonomous entrypoint for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify /deep:research:auto is documented consistently across the README, quick reference, command entrypoint, and autonomous YAML workflow. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict with the expected artifact summary.\n\nExpected signals: The same autonomous command appears across sources, autonomous mode is approval-free, and the workflow points to config, JSONL, strategy, iteration files, and `research/research.md`.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-001](01--entry-points-and-modes/auto-mode-deep-research-kickoff.md)\n\n### DR-002 | Confirm mode checkpointed execution\n\n#### Description\nVerify that confirm mode adds approval checkpoints without changing the core loop phases or artifact contract.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the confirm-mode contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify /deep:research:confirm is documented as interactive, approval-gated, and still uses the same core loop and output artifacts as auto mode. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n\nExpected signals: Confirm mode is interactive, approval-gated, and still routes through initialization, loop, synthesis, and save rather than a separate workflow.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-002](01--entry-points-and-modes/confirm-mode-checkpointed-execution.md)\n\n### DR-003 | Parameterized invocation with --max-iterations and --convergence\n\n#### Description\nVerify that the command binds topic, spec folder, execution mode, max iterations, and convergence threshold before the YAML workflow starts.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the setup-binding contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify the command entrypoint gathers required values before loading YAML and that the YAML preflight rejects missing bindings or invalid spec-folder scope. Return a concise pass/fail verdict.\n\nExpected signals: The command explicitly names topic, spec folder, execution mode, max iterations, and convergence threshold; YAML preflight verifies them before file writes.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-003](01--entry-points-and-modes/parameterized-invocation-max-iterations-convergence.md)\n\n---\n\n## 8. INITIALIZATION AND STATE SETUP\n\nThis category covers 4 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract.\n\n### DR-004 | Fresh initialization creates canonical state files\n\n#### Description\nVerify that a fresh session creates the canonical config, JSONL, and strategy files from the shipped assets.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the fresh-initialization contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify initialization creates deep-research-config.json, deep-research-state.jsonl, and deep-research-strategy.md from the live templates. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict.\n\nExpected signals: The scratch directory is created, config and strategy come from the shipped assets, and the JSONL begins with a config record.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-004](02--initialization-and-state-setup/fresh-initialization-creates-canonical-state-files.md)\n\n### DR-005 | Resume classification from valid prior state\n\n#### Description\nVerify that the workflow classifies an existing valid scratch state as resumable before writing new files.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the resume-classification contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy are inspected before new files are written and that a valid prior state skips re-initialization. Return a concise pass/fail verdict.\n\nExpected signals: A four-state classification model exists, resume skips init writes, and completed sessions route differently from active resumes.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-005](02--initialization-and-state-setup/resume-classification-from-valid-prior-state.md)\n\n### DR-006 | Invalid or contradictory state halts for repair\n\n#### Description\nVerify that partial or contradictory scratch artifacts trigger a halt for repair instead of a guessed resume path.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the invalid-state halt contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify contradictory or partial deep-research artifacts stop the workflow for repair instead of guessing through initialization. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict.\n\nExpected signals: Invalid-state is a named class, both YAML files halt with a repair message, and the docs do not promise silent guessing for contradictory state.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-006](02--initialization-and-state-setup/invalid-or-contradictory-state-halts-for-repair.md)\n\n### DR-027 | Research charter validated at init\n\n#### Description\nVerify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections after initialization.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the research charter validation contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify initialization Step 5a verifies the presence of \"Non-Goals\" and \"Stop Conditions\" sections in strategy.md, appends empty placeholders if missing, and presents the charter for user review in confirm mode. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n\nExpected signals: strategy.md has a \"## 4. Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist); strategy.md has a \"## 5. Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist); if either section is missing, it is appended as an empty placeholder; in confirm mode, the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) is presented for user review before proceeding.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-027](02--initialization-and-state-setup/research-charter-validation.md)\n\n---\n\n## 9. ITERATION EXECUTION AND STATE DISCIPLINE\n\nThis category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract.\n\n### DR-007 | Iteration reads state before research\n\n#### Description\nVerify that each dispatched iteration reads JSONL and strategy state before performing research actions.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the read-state-first iteration contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify the loop dispatch and the @deep-research agent both require reading JSONL and strategy state before any research actions. Return a concise operator verdict.\n\nExpected signals: Loop step order begins with state reads, the quick reference checklist says the same, and the agent definition starts with JSONL plus strategy reads.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-007](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/iteration-reads-state-before-research.md)\n\n### DR-008 | Iteration writes iteration-NNN.md, JSONL record, and reducer refresh\n\n#### Description\nVerify that each completed iteration writes the detailed iteration file, appends JSONL, and enables reducer-owned packet synchronization.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the iteration write-back contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify each iteration writes iteration-NNN.md, appends a JSONL iteration record, and triggers reducer-owned refresh of deep-research-strategy.md, findings-registry.json, and deep-research-dashboard.md. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n\nExpected signals: Iteration file creation, JSONL append, and reducer refresh are all mandatory parts of the loop, not optional side effects.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-008](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/iteration-writes-iteration-jsonl-and-strategy-update.md)\n\n### DR-009 | Strategy “Next Focus” and exhausted-approach discipline\n\n#### Description\nVerify that the loop honors the strategy file’s Next Focus and avoids approaches marked exhausted or blocked.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the strategy-discipline contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify iteration focus comes from Next Focus and that exhausted or blocked approaches are not retried. Return a concise user-facing verdict.\n\nExpected signals: Next Focus is read explicitly, exhausted approaches are treated as do-not-retry, and recovery mode consults deferred ideas instead of repeating blocked tactics.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-009](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/strategy-next-focus-and-exhausted-approach-discipline.md)\n\n### DR-010 | Progressive synthesis behavior for research/research.md\n\n#### Description\nVerify that `research/research.md` remains workflow-owned while progressive updates are allowed when `progressiveSynthesis` is enabled.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the progressive-synthesis contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify research/research.md is workflow-owned canonical output, that incremental updates are allowed when progressiveSynthesis is true, and that synthesis still finalizes the document. Return a concise verdict.\n\nExpected signals: The docs describe `research/research.md` as workflow-owned, `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to true, and the final synthesis phase still runs.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-010](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/progressive-synthesis-behavior-for-research-md.md)\n\n### DR-024 | Dashboard generation after iteration\n\n#### Description\nVerify dashboard.md is auto-generated after iteration evaluation with correct content.\n\n#### Scenario Contract\nPrompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the dashboard generation contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify the dashboard file is created at the correct path, contains the required sections (iteration table, question status, trend, dead ends, next focus, active risks), and is regenerated after each iteration. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n\nExpected signals: `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` exists after at least one iteration completes, contains an iteration table, question status with X/Y answered, trend with last 3 newInfoRatio values, dead ends consolidated from ruledOut data, next focus from strategy.md, and active risks.\n\n#### Test Execution\n> **Feature File:** [DR-024](03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/dashboard-generation-after-iteration.md)\n\n### DR-025 | Novelty justification present in JSONL\n\n#### Description\nVerify every iteration JSONL record includes noveltyJustification alongside newInfoRatio.\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":683,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md","time":{"start":1782532193677,"end":1782532193680}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9d95d13d2e2101016a3f4861918081919b1f8e544f160166"}},"id":"prt_f0732bd8a001UbgUS4HizSbW2U","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f073271a7001sFCL0mIWZqOuse"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782532194191,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"id":"prt_f0732bf8c0013fbmjkGZPsssXq","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"ab87b191cf288cd2cf6e378b1a7cd773ba95a6e3","messageID":"msg_f073271a7001sFCL0mIWZqOuse","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":47370,"input":17725,"output":421,"reasoning":40,"cache":{"write":0,"read":29184}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782532195721,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"id":"prt_f0732c588001UC6k5cYWv3QHPN","messageID":"msg_f0732c108001ahckgJ7f1AxoWC","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","snapshot":"ab87b191cf288cd2cf6e378b1a7cd773ba95a6e3","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1782532211540,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"id":"prt_f0732cb8f001TQl7xkAG32k23p","messageID":"msg_f0732c108001ahckgJ7f1AxoWC","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","type":"text","text":"The workflow includes a `fanout_lineage_artifact_dir` branch matching the user’s instruction; I’m following that branch without invoking the resolver. Next step is source research and packet initialization.","time":{"start":1782532197263,"end":1782532211537},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e9894becac5cafe016a3f48653fb08191be4f5a4cb7af85b4","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532211597,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3HjyZbtI4IvOvQo397SaHjyI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":781,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n781:         action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n782:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n783:         inputs:\n784:           latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n785:           newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n786:           priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n787:         outputs:\n788:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n789:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n790:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n791:         failure_modes:\n792:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n793:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n794:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n795:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n796: \n797:       step_graph_upsert:\n798:         action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n799:         read:\n800:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n801:         extract:\n802:           - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n803:           - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n804:           - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n805:           - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n806:         if_graph_events_present:\n807:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n808:           note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n809:         if_graph_events_missing:\n810:           proceed: true\n811: \n812:       step_evaluate_results:\n813:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n814:         verify:\n815:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n816:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n817:           - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n818:           - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n819:         extract:\n820:           - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n821:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n822:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n823:           - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n824:         on_missing_outputs:\n825:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n826:           # <!-- F-010-B5-02 -->\n827:           # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n828:           # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n829:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n830: \n831:       step_generate_dashboard:\n832:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n833:         read:\n834:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n835:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n836:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n837:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n838:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n839:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n840: \n841:       step_update_tracking:\n842:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n843:         set:\n844:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n845:           stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n846:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n847: \n848:       step_loop_decision:\n849:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n850:         goto: step_read_state\n851: \n852:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n853:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n854:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n855:   phase_synthesis:\n856:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n857:     steps:\n858: \n859:       step_fanout_merge:\n860:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n861:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n862:         command: |\n863:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n864:             --loop-type research \\\n865:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n866:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n867:         wait_for_completion: true\n868: \n869:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n870:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n871:         read:\n872:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n873:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n874:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n875:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n876:         extract:\n877:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n878:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n879:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n880:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n881:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n882:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n883:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n884:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n885:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n886:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n887:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n888:           - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n889: \n890:       step_read_all_iterations:\n891:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n892:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n893:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n894: \n895:       step_emit_resource_map:\n896:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n897:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n898:         read:\n899:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n900:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n901:         write:\n902:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n903:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n904: \n905:       step_compile_research:\n906:         action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n907:         instructions: |\n908:           If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n909:             1. Read current research/research.md\n910:             2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n911:             3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n912:             4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n913:             5. Add convergence report as appendix\n914:             6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n915: \n916:           If research/research.md does not exist:\n917:             1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n918:             2. Populate sections from iteration files\n919:             3. Add citations from original sources\n920:             4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n921:             5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n922:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n923:         output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n924: \n925:       step_convergence_report:\n926:         action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n927:         report: |\n928:           ## Convergence Report\n929:           - Stop reason: {reason}\n930:           - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n931:           - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n932:           - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n933:           - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n934:           - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n935:           - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n936:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"answeredCount\":{answered_count},\"totalQuestions\":{total_questions},\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n937: \n938:       step_writeback_spec_findings:\n939:         action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n940:         edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n941:         host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n942:         generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n943:         generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n944:         fail_closed_conflict_check:\n945:           if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n946:             detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n947:             on_manual_edit_conflict:\n948:               append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n949:               halt: true\n950:         instructions:\n951:           - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n952:           - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n953:           - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n954:           - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n955:           - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n956:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n957: \n958:       step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n959:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n960:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n961:         note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n962: \n963:       step_update_config_status:\n964:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n965:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n966:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n967: \n968:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n969:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n970:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n971:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n972:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n973: \n974:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n975:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n976:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n977:   phase_save:\n978:     purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n979:     steps:\n980: \n981:       step_compose_save_payload:\n982:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n983:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n984:         requirements:\n985:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n986:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n987:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n988:         example_payload: |\n989:           {\n990:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n991:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n992:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n993:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n994:             \"exchanges\": [],\n995:             \"toolCalls\": []\n996:           }\n997: \n998:       step_generate_context:\n999:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1000:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1001:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1002: \n1003:       step_index_memory:\n1004:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1005:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1006:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1007:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1008: \n1009:       step_verify_save:\n1010:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1011:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1012:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1013: \n1014:       step_release_lock:\n1015:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1016:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1017:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1018: \n1019:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1020:   # COMPLETION\n1021:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1022:   completion:\n1023:     message: |\n1024:       Deep research complete.\n1025:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1026:       Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n1027: \n1028:       Artifacts:\n1029:         - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1030:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n1031:         - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n1032:         - Memory context saved\n1033: \n1034:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1035:     next_steps:\n1036:       - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n1037:       - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n1038:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1039: \n1040: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1041: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1042: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1043: error_recovery:\n1044:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1045:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1046:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1047:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n1048: \n1049: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1050: # RULES\n1051: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1052: rules:\n1053:   ALWAYS:\n1054:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1055:     - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n1056:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1057:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1058:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1059:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1060:   NEVER:\n1061:     - skip_convergence_check\n1062:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1063:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1064:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1065:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1066:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1067: \n1068: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1069: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1070: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1071: reference_only_appendix:\n1072:   checkpoint_commit:\n1073:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1074:     commands:\n1075:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n1076:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1077:   wave_orchestration:\n1078:     note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1079:     summary:\n1080:       - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n1081:       - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n1082:       - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"\n\n(End of file - total 1082 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        inputs:\n          latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n          newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        outputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        inputs:\n          latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n          newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        outputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n        extract:\n          - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n          - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n          - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n        extract:\n          - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-02 -->\n          # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n          # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_compile_research:\n        action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n        instructions: |\n          If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n            1. Read current research/research.md\n            2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n            3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n            4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n            5. Add convergence report as appendix\n            6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n\n          If research/research.md does not exist:\n            1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n            2. Populate sections from iteration files\n            3. Add citations from original sources\n            4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n            5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n        report: |\n          ## Convergence Report\n          - Stop reason: {reason}\n          - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n          - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n          - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n          - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n          - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n          - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"answeredCount\":{answered_count},\"totalQuestions\":{total_questions},\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_writeback_spec_findings:\n        action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n        edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n        host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        fail_closed_conflict_check:\n          if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n            detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n            on_manual_edit_conflict:\n              append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              halt: true\n        instructions:\n          - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n          - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n          - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n          - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n          - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep research complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n        - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n      - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  wave_orchestration:\n    note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    summary:\n      - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n      - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n      - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"","lineStart":781,"lineEnd":1082,"totalLines":1082,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782532211581,"end":1782532211593}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e9894becac5cafe016a3f487382a48191b7c809bc2890520f"}},"id":"prt_f0733037a001hQ06NyG2seLbkC","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f0732c108001ahckgJ7f1AxoWC"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532211598,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_E5aWtqCtWRiRNUySSNRRTShp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":361,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n361:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n362:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n363:         branches:\n364:           no-spec:\n365:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n366:             seed_markers:\n367:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n368:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n369:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n370:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n371:             set:\n372:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n373:               validate_spec_doc: true\n374:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n375:           spec-present:\n376:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n377:             set:\n378:               validate_spec_doc: true\n379:             idempotency_check:\n380:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n381:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n382:               if_match:\n383:                 skip_append: true\n384:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n385:               if_no_match:\n386:                 append_only:\n387:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n388:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n389:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n390:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n391:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n392:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n393:             verify_markers:\n394:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n395:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n396:             set:\n397:               validate_spec_doc: false\n398:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n399:           conflict-detected:\n400:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n401:             halt: true\n402: \n403:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n404:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n405:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n406:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n407:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n408: \n409:       step_init_complete:\n410:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n411:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n412: \n413:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n414:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n415:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n416:   phase_loop:\n417:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n418:     repeat: true\n419:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n420:     steps:\n421: \n422:       step_read_state:\n423:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n424:         read:\n425:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n426:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n427:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n428:         extract:\n429:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n430:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n431:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n432:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n433:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n434:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n435:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n436:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n437:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n438:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n439:           - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n440:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n441:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n442:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n443:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n444:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n445:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n446:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n447: \n448:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n449:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n450:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n451:         if_exists:\n452:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n453:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n454:           halt: true\n455:         if_not_exists:\n456:           proceed: true\n457: \n458:       step_graph_convergence:\n459:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n460:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n461:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n462:         outputs:\n463:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n464:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n465:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n466:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n467:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n468:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n469:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n470: \n471:       step_check_convergence:\n472:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n473:         algorithm: |\n474:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n475:           2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n476:           3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n477:           4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n478:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n479:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n480:                signals = []\n481:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n482:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n483:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n484:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n485:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n486:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n487:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n488:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n489:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n490:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n491:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n492:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n493:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n494:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n495:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n496:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n497:                  stop_blocked = true\n498:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n499:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n500:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n501:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n502:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n503:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n504:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n505:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n506:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n507:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n508:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n509:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n510:                  stop_blocked = false\n511:           5. else: CONTINUE\n512:           6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n513:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n514:                if not guardResult.passed:\n515:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n516:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n517:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n518:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n519:         outputs:\n520:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n521:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n522:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n523:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n524:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n525:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n526:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n527:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n528:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n529:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n530:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n531:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n532: \n533:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n534:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n535:         if_blocked:\n536:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n537:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n538:           set:\n539:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n540:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n541:             stop_blocked: false\n542: \n543:       step_handle_convergence:\n544:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n545:         if_stop:\n546:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n547:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n548:         if_stuck_recovery:\n549:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n550:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n551:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n552:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n553:         if_continue:\n554:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n555: \n556:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n557:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n558:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n559:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n560:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n561:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n562:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n563:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n564:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n565: \n566:       step_marker_scan:\n567:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n568:         algorithm: |\n569:           if current_iteration > 1:\n570:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n571:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n572:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n573:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n574:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n575:                 halt with exit code 2\n576:         note: |\n577:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n578:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n579:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n580:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n581: \n582:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n583:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n584:         resolve_executor:\n585:           source: \"config.executor\"\n586:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n587:         pre_dispatch:\n588:           generate_summary: |\n589:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n590:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n591:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n592:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n593:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n594:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n595:           render_prompt_pack:\n596:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n597:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n598:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n599:             variables:\n600:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n601:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n602:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n603:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n604:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n605:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n606:               carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n607:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n608:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n609:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n610:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n611:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n612:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n613:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n614:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n615:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n616:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n617:           args:\n618:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n619:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n620:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n621:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n622:         if_native:\n623:           dispatch:\n624:             agent: deep-research\n625:             model: opus\n626:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n627:           wait_for_completion: true\n628:         if_cli_codex:\n629:           command: |\n630:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n631:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n632: \n633:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n634:             import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n635: \n636:             const executor = {\n637:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n638:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n639:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n640:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n641:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n642:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n643:             };\n644: \n645:             process.exit(\n646:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n647:                 command: 'codex',\n648:                 args: [\n649:                   'exec',\n650:                   '--model',\n651:                   executor.model,\n652:                   '-c',\n653:                   `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n654:                   '-c',\n655:                   `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n656:                   '-c',\n657:                   'approval_policy=never',\n658:                   '--sandbox',\n659:                   resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n660:                   '-',\n661:                 ],\n662:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n663:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n664:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n665:                 executor,\n666:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n667:                 input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n668:               }),\n669:             );\n670:             EOF\n671:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n672:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n673:           wait_for_completion: true\n674:         if_cli_claude_code:\n675:           command: |\n676:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n677:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n678: \n679:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n680:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n681: \n682:             const executor = {\n683:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n684:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n685:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n686:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n687:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n688:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n689:             };\n690:             const args = [\n691:               '-p',\n692:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n693:               '--model',\n694:               executor.model,\n695:               '--permission-mode',\n696:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n697:               '--output-format',\n698:               'text',\n699:             ];\n700:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n701:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n702:             }\n703: \n704:             process.exit(\n705:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n706:                 command: 'claude',\n707:                 args,\n708:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n709:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n710:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n711:                 executor,\n712:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n713:               }),\n714:             );\n715:             EOF\n716:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n717:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n718:           wait_for_completion: true\n719:           notes:\n720:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n721:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n722:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n723:         record_executor_audit:\n724:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n725:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n726:           field: \"executor\"\n727:           value:\n728:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n729:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n730:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n731:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n732:         if_cli_opencode:\n733:           command: |\n734:             opencode run \\\n735:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n736:               --format json \\\n737:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n738:               --pure \\\n739:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n740:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n741:               \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n742:               </dev/null\n743:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n744:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n745:           wait_for_completion: true\n746:           render_hint:\n747:             optional_variant_flag: |\n748:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n749:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n750:           notes:\n751:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n752:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n753:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n754:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n755:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n756:         post_dispatch_validate:\n757:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n758:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n759:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n760:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus]\n761:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n762:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n763:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n764:           on_failure:\n765:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n766:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n767:           failure_reasons_reference:\n768:             - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n769:             - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n770:             - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n771:             - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n772:             - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n773:             - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n774:             - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n775:             - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n776:             - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n777:             - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n778:             - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n779: \n780:       step_reduce_state:\n\n(Showing lines 361-780 of 1082. Use offset=781 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          5. else: CONTINUE\n          6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args: [\n                  'exec',\n                  '--model',\n                  executor.model,\n                  '-c',\n                  `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  'approval_policy=never',\n                  '--sandbox',\n                  resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n                  '-',\n                ],\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus]\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n          failure_reasons_reference:\n            - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n            - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n            - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n            - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n            - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_reduce_state:","lineStart":361,"lineEnd":780,"totalLines":1082,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782532211577,"end":1782532211596}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e9894becac5cafe016a3f4873829481919078abe2f2d76a5f"}},"id":"prt_f07330353001x9rMZ66N2M3HYd","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f0732c108001ahckgJ7f1AxoWC"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532211602,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qtfUbzfu614qy09luBb2bzT4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n3: description: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"research findings registry\"\n7:   - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n8:   - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n9:   - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n10:   - \"research dashboard derivation\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.2\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n17: \n18: The reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: The reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n39: \n40: The workflow reducer:\n41: \n42: - reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n43: - validates required iteration artifacts;\n44: - updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n45: - regenerates the findings registry;\n46: - regenerates the dashboard;\n47: - records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n48: \n49: It must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n54: \n55: The canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n56: \n57: ```json\n58: {\n59:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n60:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n61:   \"keyFindings\": [],\n62:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n63:   \"coverageBySources\": {},\n64:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n65:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n66:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n67:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n68:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n69:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: The currently documented live registry name is `deep-research-findings-registry.json` in command state paths, with `findings-registry.json` still appearing in older docs and packet examples. New docs should prefer the command state path and mention the older name only when explaining compatibility.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n78: \n79: Blocking validation:\n80: \n81: - config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n82: - every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n83: - every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n84: - JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n85: - reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n86: - convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n87: \n88: Post-dispatch failure codes include:\n89: \n90: | Code | Meaning |\n91: |------|---------|\n92: | `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n93: | `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n94: | `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n95: | `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n96: | `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n97: \n98: Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n103: \n104: Fault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n105: \n106: Safe recovery order:\n107: \n108: 1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n109: 2. Read valid JSONL records.\n110: 3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n111: 4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n112: 5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n113: 6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n114: \n115: Example reconstructed record:\n116: \n117: ```json\n118: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n124: \n125: The config may include:\n126: \n127: ```json\n128: {\n129:   \"fileProtection\": {\n130:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n131:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n132:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n133:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n134:     \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n135:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n136:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n137:   }\n138: }\n139: ```\n140: \n141: Protection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n146: \n147: Dashboard values are derived from raw state:\n148: \n149: | Dashboard Field | Source |\n150: |-----------------|--------|\n151: | iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n152: | current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n153: | convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n154: | blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n155: | graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n156: | next focus | strategy |\n157: \n158: `synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n163: \n164: The workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.\n\n(End of file - total 164 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n\n---\n\n## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n\nThe workflow reducer:\n\n- reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n- validates required iteration artifacts;\n- updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n- regenerates the findings registry;\n- regenerates the dashboard;\n- records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n\nIt must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n  \"coverageBySources\": {},\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe currently documented live registry name is `deep-research-findings-registry.json` in command state paths, with `findings-registry.json` still appearing in older docs and packet examples. New docs should prefer the command state path and mention the older name only when explaining compatibility.\n\n---\n\n## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n\nBlocking validation:\n\n- config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n- every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n- every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n- JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n- reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n- convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n\nPost-dispatch failure codes include:\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n| `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n| `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n| `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n| `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n\nThree consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n\nFault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n\nSafe recovery order:\n\n1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n2. Read valid JSONL records.\n3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n\nExample reconstructed record:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n\nThe config may include:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nProtection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n\n---\n\n## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n\nDashboard values are derived from raw state:\n\n| Dashboard Field | Source |\n|-----------------|--------|\n| iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n| current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n| convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n| blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n| graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n| next focus | strategy |\n\n`synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n\n---\n\n## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n\nThe workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":164,"totalLines":164,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1782532211584,"end":1782532211600}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e9894becac5cafe016a3f487382b081919cff9fe1d217a979"}},"id":"prt_f0733037e001YkkO7IZ9GqzWt4","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f0732c108001ahckgJ7f1AxoWC"}}
