{"type":"text","timestamp":1782532393431,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"id":"prt_f07358f06001iZ0o01eTiphM0s","messageID":"msg_f07357cc0001QonP9NvSNtAlzL","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","type":"text","text":"A prior review flagged two foundations-specific hypotheses: underspecified color-role contract and playbook/routing ambiguity. I’m checking those against the current files so the final recommendations only include confirmed issues.","time":{"start":1782532378374,"end":1782532393429},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0db324b1748963ca016a3f491a5418819189181d9ee38798ea","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532393476,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_J7Kg1BzgsDJgkYRSW8tv4Dw5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/01--color/001-oklch-palette-and-dark-mode.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/01--color/001-oklch-palette-and-dark-mode.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: OKLCH Palette And Dark Mode Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying OKLCH color planning, semantic roles, contrast repair, and dark-mode mapping.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test oklch palette\"\n6:   - \"test dark mode tokens\"\n7:   - \"foundations color scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.1\n11: expected_intent: COLOR\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/color/oklch_workflow.md\n14:   - references/color/palette_theming.md\n15: ---\n16: \n17: **Exact prompt**\n18: \n19: ```\n20: Create a color token system for a finance dashboard with a teal brand color, restrained product UI, semantic states, and dark mode.\n21: ```\n22: \n23: # FOUND-COLOR-001 | OKLCH Palette And Dark Mode\n24: \n25: ## Prompt\n26: \n27: `Create a color token system for a finance dashboard with a teal brand color, restrained product UI, semantic states, and dark mode.`\n28: \n29: ## Expected Process\n30: \n31: 1. Route to `foundations` rather than `interface`.\n32: 2. Load `references/color/oklch_workflow.md` and `references/color/palette_theming.md`.\n33: 3. Produce semantic roles before values.\n34: 4. State contrast and dark-mode rules.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Uses OKLCH or explains a compatibility exception.\n39: - Includes the canonical color roles: primary/accent, neutral, semantic, surface, border, and text.\n40: - Covers the accent states (action, selection, focus) under the primary/accent role rather than inventing a separate focus role.\n41: - Repairs contrast through lightness changes.\n42: - Dark mode uses surface lightness and semantic token remapping, not inversion.\n\n(End of file - total 42 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: OKLCH Palette And Dark Mode Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying OKLCH color planning, semantic roles, contrast repair, and dark-mode mapping.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test oklch palette\"\n  - \"test dark mode tokens\"\n  - \"foundations color scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: COLOR\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/color/oklch_workflow.md\n  - references/color/palette_theming.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nCreate a color token system for a finance dashboard with a teal brand color, restrained product UI, semantic states, and dark mode.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/01--color/001-oklch-palette-and-dark-mode.md","text":"---\ntitle: OKLCH Palette And Dark Mode Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying OKLCH color planning, semantic roles, contrast repair, and dark-mode mapping.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test oklch palette\"\n  - \"test dark mode tokens\"\n  - \"foundations color scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: COLOR\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/color/oklch_workflow.md\n  - references/color/palette_theming.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nCreate a color token system for a finance dashboard with a teal brand color, restrained product UI, semantic states, and dark mode.\n```\n\n# FOUND-COLOR-001 | OKLCH Palette And Dark Mode\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Create a color token system for a finance dashboard with a teal brand color, restrained product UI, semantic states, and dark mode.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Route to `foundations` rather than `interface`.\n2. Load `references/color/oklch_workflow.md` and `references/color/palette_theming.md`.\n3. Produce semantic roles before values.\n4. State contrast and dark-mode rules.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Uses OKLCH or explains a compatibility exception.\n- Includes the canonical color roles: primary/accent, neutral, semantic, surface, border, and text.\n- Covers the accent states (action, selection, focus) under the primary/accent role rather than inventing a separate focus role.\n- Repairs contrast through lightness changes.\n- Dark mode uses surface lightness and semantic token remapping, not inversion.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":42,"totalLines":42,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/01--color/001-oklch-palette-and-dark-mode.md","time":{"start":1782532393471,"end":1782532393475}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db324b1748963ca016a3f492962fc8191b3b34412a71e3676"}},"id":"prt_f0735c9d6001RGD0Kf01mVZwp9","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f07357cc0001QonP9NvSNtAlzL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532393518,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_PDnGgKv1uLQghFiTYoMD3qbC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/001-layout-rhythm-responsive.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/001-layout-rhythm-responsive.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Layout Rhythm And Responsive Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying spacing scale, hierarchy, grid choice, responsive adaptation, and input-context decisions.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test layout rhythm\"\n6:   - \"test responsive adaptation\"\n7:   - \"foundations layout scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.1\n11: expected_intent: LAYOUT\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/layout/layout_responsive.md\n14: ---\n15: \n16: **Exact prompt**\n17: \n18: ```\n19: Fix the layout system for a desktop dashboard that becomes a mobile task flow without hiding core controls.\n20: ```\n21: \n22: # FOUND-LAYOUT-001 | Layout Rhythm And Responsive\n23: \n24: ## Prompt\n25: \n26: `Fix the layout system for a desktop dashboard that becomes a mobile task flow without hiding core controls.`\n27: \n28: ## Expected Process\n29: \n30: 1. Route to `foundations` first; layout, spacing, and grid system decisions resolve here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n31: 2. Load `references/layout/layout_responsive.md`.\n32: 3. Define spacing scale, grouping, hierarchy, and grid behavior.\n33: 4. Adapt the experience for touch and mobile context instead of only scaling widths.\n34: \n35: ## Pass Criteria\n36: \n37: - Uses a spacing scale and proximity before adding containers.\n38: - Chooses grid/flex by structural need.\n39: - Keeps core functionality available on mobile.\n40: - Includes touch target, safe-area, orientation, and content-driven breakpoint notes.\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Layout Rhythm And Responsive Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying spacing scale, hierarchy, grid choice, responsive adaptation, and input-context decisions.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test layout rhythm\"\n  - \"test responsive adaptation\"\n  - \"foundations layout scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: LAYOUT\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/layout/layout_responsive.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nFix the layout system for a desktop dashboard that becomes a mobile task flow without hiding core controls.\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/001-layout-rhythm-responsive.md","text":"---\ntitle: Layout Rhythm And Responsive Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying spacing scale, hierarchy, grid choice, responsive adaptation, and input-context decisions.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test layout rhythm\"\n  - \"test responsive adaptation\"\n  - \"foundations layout scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: LAYOUT\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/layout/layout_responsive.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nFix the layout system for a desktop dashboard that becomes a mobile task flow without hiding core controls.\n```\n\n# FOUND-LAYOUT-001 | Layout Rhythm And Responsive\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Fix the layout system for a desktop dashboard that becomes a mobile task flow without hiding core controls.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Route to `foundations` first; layout, spacing, and grid system decisions resolve here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n2. Load `references/layout/layout_responsive.md`.\n3. Define spacing scale, grouping, hierarchy, and grid behavior.\n4. Adapt the experience for touch and mobile context instead of only scaling widths.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Uses a spacing scale and proximity before adding containers.\n- Chooses grid/flex by structural need.\n- Keeps core functionality available on mobile.\n- Includes touch target, safe-area, orientation, and content-driven breakpoint notes.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":40,"totalLines":40,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/001-layout-rhythm-responsive.md","time":{"start":1782532393503,"end":1782532393507}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db324b1748963ca016a3f49296310819183d18daa8f74c84b"}},"id":"prt_f0735ca12001TdQMvmRPArp7lo","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f07357cc0001QonP9NvSNtAlzL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532393563,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Erqt1H9CU2qvgtqbTUkyFKEW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/05--tokens/001-token-starter-handoff.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/05--tokens/001-token-starter-handoff.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Token Starter Handoff Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying the fill-in token scaffold for an OKLCH ramp, type scale and spacing scale keyed to the register.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test token starter\"\n6:   - \"test token scaffold handoff\"\n7:   - \"foundations token scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.1\n11: expected_intent: TOKENS\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - assets/token_starter.md\n14: ---\n15: \n16: **Exact prompt**\n17: \n18: ```\n19: Scaffold a token system for a restrained product UI with a teal brand hue and dark mode, ready to hand to sk-code.\n20: ```\n21: \n22: # FOUND-TOKEN-001 | Token Starter Handoff\n23: \n24: ## Prompt\n25: \n26: `Scaffold a token system for a restrained product UI with a teal brand hue and dark mode, ready to hand to sk-code.`\n27: \n28: ## Expected Process\n29: \n30: 1. Route to `foundations` first. The token scaffold is filled here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n31: 2. Read `../shared/register.md` first, then load `assets/token_starter.md`.\n32: 3. Set the register and copy the color strategy and density answers into the scaffold.\n33: 4. Fill the OKLCH ramp, type scale and spacing scale, pulling the brand hue from evidence rather than a default.\n34: 5. Fill the dark-mode block as its own surface system rather than inverted light values.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Reads the register before filling values, and lets the register win on posture when a value conflicts.\n39: - Fills every color token with an OKLCH value or a deliberate compatibility reason.\n40: - Tints neutrals toward the brand hue with a small chroma rather than using flat gray.\n41: - Sets type roles before sizes, keeps body near 16 px, and uses tabular numerals on data.\n42: - Pulls every spacing value from the scale rather than typing one-off numbers.\n43: - Builds dark mode from its own surface and text pairs, holding hue and chroma steady while varying lightness.\n44: - Confirms the handoff checklist before passing the filled scaffold to `sk-code`.\n45: - Defers channel mechanics, contrast repair and semantic role theory to the color and type references.\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Token Starter Handoff Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying the fill-in token scaffold for an OKLCH ramp, type scale and spacing scale keyed to the register.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test token starter\"\n  - \"test token scaffold handoff\"\n  - \"foundations token scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: TOKENS\nexpected_resources:\n  - assets/token_starter.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nScaffold a token system for a restrained product UI with a teal brand hue and dark mode, ready to hand to sk-code.\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/05--tokens/001-token-starter-handoff.md","text":"---\ntitle: Token Starter Handoff Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying the fill-in token scaffold for an OKLCH ramp, type scale and spacing scale keyed to the register.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test token starter\"\n  - \"test token scaffold handoff\"\n  - \"foundations token scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: TOKENS\nexpected_resources:\n  - assets/token_starter.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nScaffold a token system for a restrained product UI with a teal brand hue and dark mode, ready to hand to sk-code.\n```\n\n# FOUND-TOKEN-001 | Token Starter Handoff\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Scaffold a token system for a restrained product UI with a teal brand hue and dark mode, ready to hand to sk-code.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Route to `foundations` first. The token scaffold is filled here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n2. Read `../shared/register.md` first, then load `assets/token_starter.md`.\n3. Set the register and copy the color strategy and density answers into the scaffold.\n4. Fill the OKLCH ramp, type scale and spacing scale, pulling the brand hue from evidence rather than a default.\n5. Fill the dark-mode block as its own surface system rather than inverted light values.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Reads the register before filling values, and lets the register win on posture when a value conflicts.\n- Fills every color token with an OKLCH value or a deliberate compatibility reason.\n- Tints neutrals toward the brand hue with a small chroma rather than using flat gray.\n- Sets type roles before sizes, keeps body near 16 px, and uses tabular numerals on data.\n- Pulls every spacing value from the scale rather than typing one-off numbers.\n- Builds dark mode from its own surface and text pairs, holding hue and chroma steady while varying lightness.\n- Confirms the handoff checklist before passing the filled scaffold to `sk-code`.\n- Defers channel mechanics, contrast repair and semantic role theory to the color and type references.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":45,"totalLines":45,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/05--tokens/001-token-starter-handoff.md","time":{"start":1782532393558,"end":1782532393562}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db324b1748963ca016a3f4929631c8191981f9ea6a3e39a75"}},"id":"prt_f0735ca20001nFRUqNLpaki7IR","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f07357cc0001QonP9NvSNtAlzL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532393674,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_CaSj7SOsCwkfZimOjqYNH2e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/02--type/001-type-roles-and-measure.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/02--type/001-type-roles-and-measure.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Type Roles And Measure Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying role-based typography, scale, pairing, measure, and data text guidance.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test typography roles\"\n6:   - \"test type measure\"\n7:   - \"foundations type scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.1\n11: expected_intent: TYPE\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/type/typography_system.md\n14: ---\n15: \n16: **Exact prompt**\n17: \n18: ```\n19: Define typography for a dense analytics app with long labels, metrics, and a small marketing header.\n20: ```\n21: \n22: # FOUND-TYPE-001 | Type Roles And Measure\n23: \n24: ## Prompt\n25: \n26: `Define typography for a dense analytics app with long labels, metrics, and a small marketing header.`\n27: \n28: ## Expected Process\n29: \n30: 1. Load `references/type/typography_system.md`.\n31: 2. Define display, heading, body, caption, utility, and data roles.\n32: 3. Name measure and line-height constraints.\n33: 4. Include tabular numerals for metrics.\n34: \n35: ## Pass Criteria\n36: \n37: - Does not pick fonts before roles.\n38: - Keeps expressive display type limited to identity moments.\n39: - Addresses long labels and localization expansion.\n40: - Provides implementable role guidance for `sk-code`.\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Type Roles And Measure Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying role-based typography, scale, pairing, measure, and data text guidance.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test typography roles\"\n  - \"test type measure\"\n  - \"foundations type scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: TYPE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/type/typography_system.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nDefine typography for a dense analytics app with long labels, metrics, and a small marketing header.\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/02--type/001-type-roles-and-measure.md","text":"---\ntitle: Type Roles And Measure Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying role-based typography, scale, pairing, measure, and data text guidance.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test typography roles\"\n  - \"test type measure\"\n  - \"foundations type scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: TYPE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/type/typography_system.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nDefine typography for a dense analytics app with long labels, metrics, and a small marketing header.\n```\n\n# FOUND-TYPE-001 | Type Roles And Measure\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Define typography for a dense analytics app with long labels, metrics, and a small marketing header.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Load `references/type/typography_system.md`.\n2. Define display, heading, body, caption, utility, and data roles.\n3. Name measure and line-height constraints.\n4. Include tabular numerals for metrics.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Does not pick fonts before roles.\n- Keeps expressive display type limited to identity moments.\n- Addresses long labels and localization expansion.\n- Provides implementable role guidance for `sk-code`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":40,"totalLines":40,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/02--type/001-type-roles-and-measure.md","time":{"start":1782532393671,"end":1782532393674}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db324b1748963ca016a3f492963248191839a33b97807957c"}},"id":"prt_f0735ca8a001y4auGB9TjP7iV9","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f07357cc0001QonP9NvSNtAlzL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532393718,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_y6S3xQSs3MGmznrn3WM1hbvx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/002-context-adaptation-matrix.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/002-context-adaptation-matrix.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Context Adaptation Matrix Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying per-context rethinking across device, input and posture rather than pixel scaling.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test adaptation matrix\"\n6:   - \"test device context adaptation\"\n7:   - \"foundations adaptation scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.1\n11: expected_intent: ADAPTATION\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/layout/adaptation_matrix.md\n14: ---\n15: \n16: **Exact prompt**\n17: \n18: ```\n19: Adapt a desktop admin tool for phone, tablet and a print export without dropping any core control.\n20: ```\n21: \n22: # FOUND-LAYOUT-002 | Context Adaptation Matrix\n23: \n24: ## Prompt\n25: \n26: `Adapt a desktop admin tool for phone, tablet and a print export without dropping any core control.`\n27: \n28: ## Expected Process\n29: \n30: 1. Route to `foundations` first. Context adaptation resolves here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n31: 2. Load `references/layout/adaptation_matrix.md`.\n32: 3. Read the four adaptation dimensions before deciding what changes, device and viewport, input method, connection and capability, usage posture.\n33: 4. Rethink layout, interaction, content and navigation per target context instead of scaling the desktop design down.\n34: 5. Branch on input capability with feature queries, not on width alone.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Treats each context as a rethink across layout, interaction, content and navigation, not a shrink.\n39: - Detects input capability rather than inferring it from screen width.\n40: - Keeps every core function available on phone, tablet, desktop and print.\n41: - Never puts functionality behind hover alone and accounts for safe areas.\n42: - Produces a print or export view that removes interaction, expands hidden content and adds page context.\n43: - Uses content-driven breakpoints and serves responsive image weights.\n44: - Defers the spacing scale and container-query mechanics to `layout_responsive.md` rather than re-deriving them.\n\n(End of file - total 44 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Context Adaptation Matrix Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying per-context rethinking across device, input and posture rather than pixel scaling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test adaptation matrix\"\n  - \"test device context adaptation\"\n  - \"foundations adaptation scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: ADAPTATION\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/layout/adaptation_matrix.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nAdapt a desktop admin tool for phone, tablet and a print export without dropping any core control.\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/002-context-adaptation-matrix.md","text":"---\ntitle: Context Adaptation Matrix Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying per-context rethinking across device, input and posture rather than pixel scaling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test adaptation matrix\"\n  - \"test device context adaptation\"\n  - \"foundations adaptation scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: ADAPTATION\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/layout/adaptation_matrix.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nAdapt a desktop admin tool for phone, tablet and a print export without dropping any core control.\n```\n\n# FOUND-LAYOUT-002 | Context Adaptation Matrix\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Adapt a desktop admin tool for phone, tablet and a print export without dropping any core control.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Route to `foundations` first. Context adaptation resolves here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n2. Load `references/layout/adaptation_matrix.md`.\n3. Read the four adaptation dimensions before deciding what changes, device and viewport, input method, connection and capability, usage posture.\n4. Rethink layout, interaction, content and navigation per target context instead of scaling the desktop design down.\n5. Branch on input capability with feature queries, not on width alone.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Treats each context as a rethink across layout, interaction, content and navigation, not a shrink.\n- Detects input capability rather than inferring it from screen width.\n- Keeps every core function available on phone, tablet, desktop and print.\n- Never puts functionality behind hover alone and accounts for safe areas.\n- Produces a print or export view that removes interaction, expands hidden content and adds page context.\n- Uses content-driven breakpoints and serves responsive image weights.\n- Defers the spacing scale and container-query mechanics to `layout_responsive.md` rather than re-deriving them.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":44,"totalLines":44,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/03--layout/002-context-adaptation-matrix.md","time":{"start":1782532393713,"end":1782532393717}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db324b1748963ca016a3f4929632c8191bab28855053d8bdd"}},"id":"prt_f0735cadd001175H646200VVvw","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f07357cc0001QonP9NvSNtAlzL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532393897,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fBVJ0DzCdExnE24a8BZo0XRU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/04--data-viz/001-chart-encoding-and-color.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/04--data-viz/001-chart-encoding-and-color.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Data Visualization Encoding And Color Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying chart-type selection, axis honesty, color-for-data scale choice and data-table alignment.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test data visualization\"\n6:   - \"test chart encoding\"\n7:   - \"foundations data-viz scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.1\n11: expected_intent: DATA_VIZ\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/data_viz.md\n14: ---\n15: \n16: **Exact prompt**\n17: \n18: ```\n19: Design the data visualization layer for a finance dashboard: a metric trend, a category comparison, a density map and a numeric table.\n20: ```\n21: \n22: # FOUND-DATAVIZ-001 | Data Visualization Encoding And Color\n23: \n24: ## Prompt\n25: \n26: `Design the data visualization layer for a finance dashboard: a metric trend, a category comparison, a density map and a numeric table.`\n27: \n28: ## Expected Process\n29: \n30: 1. Route to `foundations` first. Chart encoding and color-for-data decisions resolve here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n31: 2. Load `references/data_viz.md`.\n32: 3. Match each chart to the question rather than the dataset shape, trend to a line, comparison to a bar, density to a sequential scale.\n33: 4. Choose the color-for-data scale type per question and keep data color separate from brand color.\n34: 5. Align the numeric table with right-aligned columns and tabular numerals.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Picks the chart from the question, comparison, trend, part-to-whole, distribution or relationship.\n39: - Starts bar value axes at zero and labels any non-zero line baseline.\n40: - Encodes one variable per visual channel.\n41: - Selects the scale type correctly, sequential for magnitude, diverging for a real midpoint, categorical for unordered groups, capped near six to eight hues.\n42: - Never makes color the only carrier of meaning, and keeps one color meaning across every view.\n43: - Right-aligns numeric columns with tabular numerals and consistent decimals.\n44: - Provides a non-chart alternative for small screens and assistive technology.\n45: - Defers OKLCH channel mechanics and contrast repair to the color references rather than re-deriving them.\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Data Visualization Encoding And Color Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying chart-type selection, axis honesty, color-for-data scale choice and data-table alignment.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test data visualization\"\n  - \"test chart encoding\"\n  - \"foundations data-viz scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: DATA_VIZ\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/data_viz.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nDesign the data visualization layer for a finance dashboard: a metric trend, a category comparison, a density map and a numeric table.\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/04--data-viz/001-chart-encoding-and-color.md","text":"---\ntitle: Data Visualization Encoding And Color Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying chart-type selection, axis honesty, color-for-data scale choice and data-table alignment.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test data visualization\"\n  - \"test chart encoding\"\n  - \"foundations data-viz scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.1\nexpected_intent: DATA_VIZ\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/data_viz.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nDesign the data visualization layer for a finance dashboard: a metric trend, a category comparison, a density map and a numeric table.\n```\n\n# FOUND-DATAVIZ-001 | Data Visualization Encoding And Color\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Design the data visualization layer for a finance dashboard: a metric trend, a category comparison, a density map and a numeric table.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Route to `foundations` first. Chart encoding and color-for-data decisions resolve here before any `sk-code` implementation handoff.\n2. Load `references/data_viz.md`.\n3. Match each chart to the question rather than the dataset shape, trend to a line, comparison to a bar, density to a sequential scale.\n4. Choose the color-for-data scale type per question and keep data color separate from brand color.\n5. Align the numeric table with right-aligned columns and tabular numerals.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Picks the chart from the question, comparison, trend, part-to-whole, distribution or relationship.\n- Starts bar value axes at zero and labels any non-zero line baseline.\n- Encodes one variable per visual channel.\n- Selects the scale type correctly, sequential for magnitude, diverging for a real midpoint, categorical for unordered groups, capped near six to eight hues.\n- Never makes color the only carrier of meaning, and keeps one color meaning across every view.\n- Right-aligns numeric columns with tabular numerals and consistent decimals.\n- Provides a non-chart alternative for small screens and assistive technology.\n- Defers OKLCH channel mechanics and contrast repair to the color references rather than re-deriving them.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":45,"totalLines":45,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/04--data-viz/001-chart-encoding-and-color.md","time":{"start":1782532393893,"end":1782532393896}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db324b1748963ca016a3f492963308191b43ac7f3f86bbb40"}},"id":"prt_f0735cb3f001ZTPbRxRF9jiH9C","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c98ffelEEBfNvFj3hize","messageID":"msg_f07357cc0001QonP9NvSNtAlzL"}}
