would likely improve the Mode A score?\",\n+    \"Which reference or asset additions improve usefulness without duplication?\",\n+    \"What tooling or validation changes are warranted?\",\n+    \"What should explicitly not be done?\"\n+  ],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"FND-001\",\n+      \"title\": \"Actual foundations packet is design-foundations\",\n+      \"finding\": \"The mode name is foundations, but the packet path is `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/`.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:23-29\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json:27-37\"],\n+      \"priority\": \"context\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"FND-002\",\n+      \"title\": \"009 foundations additions have landed\",\n+      \"finding\": \"Data visualization, adaptation matrix, and token starter are present and wired, so improvement should not re-add those basics.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/012-foundations-motion-audit/implementation-summary.md:57-76\"],\n+      \"priority\": \"context\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"FND-003\",\n+      \"title\": \"Parent aliases under-cover foundations axes\",\n+      \"finding\": \"Parent foundations aliases omit child trigger vocabulary for data visualization, adaptation, grids, container queries, and token starter.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json:27-37\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:31-32\"],\n+      \"priority\": \"P1\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"FND-004\",\n+      \"title\": \"Token route underloads cross-axis context\",\n+      \"finding\": \"The loading table calls token work cross-axis, but the pseudocode TOKENS map loads only corpus_map and token_starter.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:92-93\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:115-122\"],\n+      \"priority\": \"P1\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"FND-005\",\n+      \"title\": \"Register step needs a local intake/handoff surface\",\n+      \"finding\": \"The shared register is required before foundations, but the router inventory only discovers resources under foundations references/assets.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/register.md:16-29\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:140-145\"],\n+      \"priority\": \"P2\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"FND-006\",\n+      \"title\": \"Handoff needs a final sk-code-ready schema\",\n+      \"finding\": \"The token starter is a good fill-in scaffold but lacks a final implementation handoff block with CSS variables, breakpoints, verification evidence, and risks.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/assets/token_starter.md:122-132\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:309-317\"],\n+      \"priority\": \"P2\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"FND-007\",\n+      \"title\": \"Manual scenarios are ready for benchmark linkage\",\n+      \"finding\": \"The playbook already has expected_intent and expected_resources metadata, but no executed results matrix ties it to routing confidence.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:28-38\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/README.md:124-130\"],\n+      \"priority\": \"P2\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Another OKLCH or dark-mode basics guide\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Current references already cover channel mechanics, contrast repair, gamut, semantic roles, and dark mode.\",\n+      \"evidence\": \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/references/color/oklch_workflow.md:58-70\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Split foundations into color/layout/type child skills now\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Out of scope for this improvement pass and explicitly ruled out in 009.\",\n+      \"evidence\": \"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/research.md:82\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Bulk-import the external corpus\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Prior research concluded the leverage is operational references and cards, not volume.\",\n+      \"evidence\": \"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/research.md:16-18\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"coverageBySources\": {\n+    \"skill\": 2,\n+    \"registry\": 1,\n+    \"references\": 6,\n+    \"assets\": 1,\n+    \"manual_testing_playbook\": 6,\n+    \"prior_research\": 3,\n+    \"implementation_phase\": 2\n+  },\n+  \"convergenceScore\": 0.7,\n+  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n+  \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n+  \"graphDecision\": null,\n+  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-27T03:54:00Z\"\n+}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/002-foundations/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/002-foundations/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/002-foundations/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,52 @@\n+# Deep Research Dashboard - gpt55fast Foundations\n+\n+## Lifecycle\n+\n+- Session ID: `fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104407-